Subject: Re: [T2] making valve cover gaskets stick to valve covers

On 6/8/03 12:02 PM, "Jasan C." <type2-78(-at-)attbi.com> wrote:

> I dont use any type of glue. That just makes it harder to clean up the
> surfaces when it comes time for new gaskets. I smear a very thin layer of
> your every day wheel bearing grease on both sides of the gasket. Helps them
> stick and wont harm the internals of the valve assembly. You dont have to
> use alot, just enough to help them stick.

Don't use grease. This allow the gasket to get "sucked" and you'll end up
with leaks.

Although grease seals you want to use something that keeps the gasket from
moving. Grease will never do that. Here's a sucked gasket that was applied
with a light coat of wheel bearing grease:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Maintenance2/216-WarpedGasket.jpg

